<subSubSection id="C36380BD8B4AE01BFEAFFA44FE0EF959" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC6D3368B4AE01BFEAFFA44FE0EF959" blockId="3.[264,1324,284,1870]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4AE01BFEAFFA44FE00F9F9" bold="true" box="[312,483,1524,1550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Comments.—</emphasis>
The Oriental 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4AE01BFD14FA44FCE1F9F9" authorityName=", Oriental" box="[643,770,1524,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bethylidae</taxonomicName>
fauna is poorly known, with few keys to species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8AEC78B4AE01BFED2F9ACFDF1F9C1" author="Terayama, M." box="[325,530,1564,1590]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref2326" refString="Terayama, M. (1993) Check list of Bethylidae of the Oriental and the Southeastern part of Palaearctic regions (Insecta, Hymenoptera). Bulletin of the Toho Gakuen, 8, 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1993">Terayama (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, in a bethylid checklist of the Oriental and the southeastern part of Palaearctic regions, cataloged just 16 species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4AE01BFCA8F9F4FC49F9AA" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[831,938,1604,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4AE01BFCA8F9F4FC49F9AA" box="[831,938,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Apenesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including three from 
<collectingCountry id="F36E93A68B4AE01BFB25F9F4FB11F9A9" box="[1202,1266,1604,1630]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">India</collectingCountry>
. The majority of these species were poorly described about 100 years ago, which makes them difficult to identify.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36380BD8B4AE01CFEAFF90CFE4CFD69" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BC6D3368B4AE01CFEAFF90CFC0BFE59" blockId="3.[264,1324,284,1870]" lastBlockId="4.[264,1324,284,1070]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4AE01BFEAFF90CFDD2F922" authority="Azevedo &amp; Waichert, 2006" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Waichert" authorityYear="2006" box="[312,561,1724,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadrica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4AE01BFEAFF90CFDD2F922" box="[312,561,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Apenesia sahyadrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23EB25F8B4AE01BFDABF90CFD78F921" box="[572,667,1724,1750]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from others species in the genus, because the punctuation is sparse and shallow, and the propodeal disc lacks a carina. Aside from these characteristics, 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4AE01BFE28F8BCFD81F8D2" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Waichert" authorityYear="2006" box="[447,610,1804,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadrica">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4AE01BFE28F8BCFD81F8D2" box="[447,610,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">A. sahyadrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4AE01BFD70F8BCFBB3F8D1" authority="(Fouts, 1930)" authorityName="Fouts" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Fouts" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[743,1104,1804,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaensis">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4AE01BFD70F8BCFC49F8D2" box="[743,938,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">A. mindanaensis</emphasis>
(Fouts, 1930)
</taxonomicName>
but it differs from it by the different coloration, that is rufous in 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4AE01BFCB7F884FC01F8BA" baseAuthorityName="Fouts" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[800,994,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaensis">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4AE01BFCB7F884FC01F8BA" box="[800,994,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">A. mindanaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and black in 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4AE01BFB17F884FAC0F8BA" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Waichert" authorityYear="2006" box="[1152,1315,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadrica">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4AE01BFB17F884FAC0F8BA" box="[1152,1315,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">A. sahyadrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFE9FFEACFDC7FEC1" authority="(Kieffer, 1913)" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Kieffer" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[264,548,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFE9FFEACFE8DFEC2" box="[264,366,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">A. minor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8AEC78B4DE01CFEEBFEACFDFFFEC1" author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[380,540,284,310]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" pagination="253 - 260" refId="ref2152" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1913) Serphides des iles Philippines. Insecta, 3, 31, 253 - 260." type="journal article" year="1913">Kieffer, 1913</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
has the clypeus truncate, with a sharpened tooth in the apex, mandibles with one tooth and a pterostigma vein, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFC01FEF4FBD9FEAA" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Waichert" authorityYear="2006" box="[918,1082,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadrica">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFC01FEF4FBD9FEAA" box="[918,1082,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">A. sahyadrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp nov. has clypeus rounded, mandibles with three teeth and absence of pterostigma vein. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFBA0FEDCFB35FE72" box="[1079,1238,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="percurrens">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFBA0FEDCFB35FE72" box="[1079,1238,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">A. percurrens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFEC3FE24FE14FE5A" authority="Azevedo &amp; Waichert, 2006" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Waichert" authorityYear="2006" box="[340,503,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadrica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFEC3FE24FE14FE5A" box="[340,503,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">A. sahyadrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23EB25F8B4DE01CFE68FE24FDBAFE59" box="[511,601,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but there is not posmarginal vein.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6D3368B4DE01CFEAFFE0CFE4CFD69" blockId="4.[264,1324,284,1070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
The sex association in 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFDD0FE0CFD50FE22" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[583,691,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFDD0FE0CFD50FE22" box="[583,691,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Apenesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is difficult because of the strong sexual dimorphism. Presently, there is only one confirmed association between male and female of any species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFEBDFDBCFE75FDD2" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[298,406,524,549]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFEBDFDBCFE75FDD2" box="[298,406,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Apenesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8AEC78B4DE01CFE30FDBCFD96FDD1" author="Krombein, K. V." box="[423,629,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" pagination="620 - 631" refId="ref2176" refString="Krombein, K. V. (1989) Systematic notes on some Bethylidae from Botswana: Pristocerinae (Hymenoptera: Aculeata). Entomological Society of Washington. Proceedings, 91 (4), 620 - 631." type="journal article" year="1989">Krombein (1989)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFD6EFDBCFB7AFDD1" authority="Krombein (1989)" authorityName="Krombein" authorityYear="1989" box="[761,1177,524,550]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forchhammeri">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFD6EFDBCFC22FDD2" box="[761,961,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">A. forchhammeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8AEC78B4DE01CFC5CFDBCFB7AFDD1" author="Krombein, K. V." box="[971,1177,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" pagination="620 - 631" refId="ref2176" refString="Krombein, K. V. (1989) Systematic notes on some Bethylidae from Botswana: Pristocerinae (Hymenoptera: Aculeata). Entomological Society of Washington. Proceedings, 91 (4), 620 - 631." type="journal article" year="1989">Krombein (1989)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from a pair taken in copula in a Malaise trap. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8AEC78B4DE01CFD0DFD84FCA6FDB9" author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[666,837,564,590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" pagination="253 - 260" refId="ref2152" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1913) Serphides des iles Philippines. Insecta, 3, 31, 253 - 260." type="journal article" year="1913">Kieffer (1913)</bibRefCitation>
described both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFBFEFD84FAC0FDBA" box="[1129,1315,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippinenis">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFBFEFD84FAC0FDBA" box="[1129,1315,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">A. philippinenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the association was not justified. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFD2BFDECFCBCFD82" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Waichert" authorityYear="2006" box="[700,863,604,629]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadrica">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFD2BFDECFCBCFD82" box="[700,863,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">A. sahyadrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described from both sexes reared on the same host.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36380BD8B4DE01CFEAFFD1CFAE7FCC9" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC6D3368B4DE01CFEAFFD1CFAE7FCC9" blockId="4.[264,1324,284,1070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Females 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFE33FD1CFDECFD32" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[420,527,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFE33FD1CFDECFD32" box="[420,527,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Apenesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are rarely collected. The few described females are apterous and smaller than the male. Nevertheless, the females studied in this paper are unusually big. They are slightly larger than the males, other differences being the clypeus truncate in females and rounded in males, two big teeth in mandibles in females and five in males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36380BD8B4DE01CFEAFFCFCFEAFFBD9" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BC6D3368B4DE01CFEAFFCFCFBD0FC41" blockId="4.[264,1324,284,1070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFEAFFCFCFE7FFC91" bold="true" box="[312,412,844,870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Biology.</emphasis>
—This species was extracted from the tunnels of the coffee white stem borer, 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFE9FFCC4FDF4FC79" authority="Chevrolat" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1863" box="[264,535,884,910]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xylotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripes">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFE9FFCC4FE7EFC7A" box="[264,413,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">X. quadripes</emphasis>
Chevrolat
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFDB1FCC4FD4FFC79" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[550,684,884,910]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFD20FCC4FC85FC79" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[695,870,884,910]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cerambycidae</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C79A8B58B4DE01CFCEFFCC4FB8FFC7A" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Waichert" authorityYear="2006" box="[888,1132,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadrica">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFCEFFCC4FB8FFC7A" box="[888,1132,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Apenesia sahyadrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is being used as an important natural enemy of this stem borer in coffee crop in 
<collectingCountry id="F36E93A68B4DE01CFC78FC2CFBCCFC41" box="[1007,1071,924,950]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6D3368B4DE01CFEAFFC74FEAFFBD9" blockId="4.[264,1324,284,1070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B90D0F248B4DE01CFEAFFC74FE0BFC29" bold="true" box="[312,488,964,990]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Etymogeny.—</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the area name in Indian classical Sanskrit where the specimens were collected, Sahyadri, a coffee growing area in Western ghats of 
<collectingCountry id="F36E93A68B4DE01CFE9FFBA4FEABFBD9" box="[264,328,1044,1070]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
